{"name": "vsdehalo", "metadata": {"name": "vsdehalo", "version": "1.9.2", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["VapourSynth", "vstools", "vskernels", "vsexprtools", "vsrgtools", "vsmasktools", "vsaa", "vsscale", "vsdenoise"], "summary": "Collection of dehaloing VapourSynth functions", "upload_time": 1733468914}, "documentation": ["# vs-dehalo\n\nCollection of dehaloing VapourSynth functions\n\n## How to use\n\n```py\nfrom vsdehalo import fine_dehalo\n\nsrc = ...\n\ndehaloed = fine_dehalo(src)\n```\n\n## How to install\n\nInstall `vsdehalo` with the following command:\n\n```sh\npip install vsdehalo\n```\n\nOr if you want the latest git version, install it with this command:\n\n```sh\npip install git+https://github.com/Jaded-Encoding-Thaumaturgy/vs-dehalo.git\n```\n\n<br>\n"], "modules": [{"name": "vsdehalo.denoise", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "vsdehalo.denoise.smooth_dering", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "clip", "type": {"name": "vs.VideoNode", "xref": {"fqname": "vstools.vs.VideoNode", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "smooth", "type": {"name": "vs.VideoNode | Prefilter", "xref": null, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "ringmask", "type": {"name": "vs.VideoNode | None", "xref": null, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "mrad", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "msmooth", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "minp", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "mthr", "type": {"name": "float", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.float", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "incedge", "type": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "thr", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "elast", "type": {"name": "float", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.float", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "darkthr", "type": {"name": "int | None", "xref": null, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "contra", "type": {"name": "int | float | bool", "xref": null, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "drrep", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "pre_ss", "type": {"name": "float", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.float", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "pre_supersampler", "type": {"name": "ScalerT", "xref": {"fqname": "vskernels.ScalerT", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "pre_downscaler", "type": {"name": "ScalerT", "xref": {"fqname": "vskernels.ScalerT", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "planes", "type": {"name": "PlanesT", "xref": {"fqname": "vstools.PlanesT", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "show_mask", "type": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "vs.VideoNode", "xref": {"fqname": "vstools.vs.VideoNode", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["---\nparam clip: Clip to process.\nparam contra: |-\n  Whether to use contra-sharpening to resharp deringed clip:\n  False: no contrasharpening\n  True: auto radius for contrasharpening\n  int 1-3: represents radius for contrasharpening\n  float: represents level for contrasharpening_dehalo\nparam darkthr: |-\n  Threshold (8-bit scale) for darker area near edges, for filtering diff\n  that brightening the image by default equals to thr/4.\n  Set it lower if you think de-ringing destroys too much lines, etc.\n  When darkthr is not equal to `thr`, `thr` limits darkening,\n  while `darkthr` limits brightening.\n  This is useful to limit the overshoot/undershoot/blurring introduced in deringing.\n  Examples:\n\n  > `thr=0`, `darkthr=0` : no limiting\n  > `thr=255`, `darkthr=255`: no limiting\n  > `thr=8`, `darkthr=2` : limit darkening with 8, brightening is limited to 2\n  > `thr=8`, `darkthr=0` : limit darkening with 8, brightening is limited to 0\n  > `thr=255`, `darkthr=0` : limit darkening with 255, brightening is limited to 0\n  > For the last two examples, output will remain unchanged. (0/255: no limiting)\nparam drrep: Use repair for details retention, recommended values are 13/12/1.\nparam elast: |-\n  Elasticity of the soft threshold.\n  Larger \"elast\" will result in more pixels being blended from.\nparam incedge: Whether to include edge in ring mask, by default ring mask only include\n  area near edges.\nparam kwargs: Kwargs to be passed to the prefilter function.\nparam minp: Inpanding iterations of prewitt edge mask, higher value means more aggressive\n  processing.\nparam mrad: Expanding iterations of edge mask, higher value means more aggressive\n  processing.\nparam msmooth: Inflating iterations of edge mask, higher value means smoother edges\n  of mask.\nparam mthr: |-\n  Threshold of prewitt edge mask, lower value means more aggressive processing\n  but for strong ringing, lower value will treat some ringing as edge,\n  which \"protects\" this ringing from being processed.\nparam planes: Planes to be processed.\nparam ringmask: Custom ringing mask.\nparam show_mask: Show the computed ringing mask.\nparam smooth: Already smoothed clip, or a Prefilter, tuple for [luma, chroma] prefilter.\nparam thr: |-\n  Threshold (8-bit scale) to limit filtering diff.\n  Smaller thr will result in more pixels being taken from processed clip.\n  Larger thr will result in less pixels being taken from input clip.\n\n  > PDiff: pixel value diff between processed clip and input clip\n  > ODiff: pixel value diff between output clip and input clip\n  > PDiff, thr and elast is used to calculate ODiff:\n  > ODiff = PDiff when [PDiff \\<= thr]\n  > ODiff gradually smooths from thr to 0 when [thr \\<= PDiff \\<= thr * elast]\n  > For elast>2.0, ODiff reaches maximum when [PDiff == thr * elast / 2]\n  > ODiff = 0 when [PDiff >= thr * elast]\nreturn: Deringed clip.\n---\n"]}, {"name": "vsdehalo.denoise.vine_dehalo", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "clip", "type": {"name": "vs.VideoNode", "xref": {"fqname": "vstools.vs.VideoNode", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "strength", "type": {"name": "float | Sequence[float]", "xref": null, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "sharp", "type": {"name": "float", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.float", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "sigma", "type": {"name": "float | list[float]", "xref": null, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "supersampler", "type": {"name": "ScalerT", "xref": {"fqname": "vskernels.ScalerT", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "downscaler", "type": {"name": "ScalerT", "xref": {"fqname": "vskernels.ScalerT", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "planes", "type": {"name": "PlanesT", "xref": {"fqname": "vstools.PlanesT", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "vs.VideoNode", "xref": {"fqname": "vstools.vs.VideoNode", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["---\nparam clip: Clip to process.\nparam downscaler: Scaler used for downscaling after supersampling.\nparam kwargs: Additional kwargs to be passed to nl_means.\nparam planes: Planes to be processed.\nparam sharp: Weight to blend supersampled clip.\nparam sigma: Gaussian sigma for filtering cutoff.\nparam strength: Strength of nl_means filtering.\nparam supersampler: Scaler used for supersampling before dehaloing.\nreturn: Dehaloed clip.\n---\n"]}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "vsdehalo.denoise.smooth_dering", "xref": {"fqname": "vsdehalo.denoise.smooth_dering", "project": null}}, {"name": "vsdehalo.denoise.vine_dehalo", "xref": {"fqname": "vsdehalo.denoise.vine_dehalo", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "vsdehalo._metadata", "documentation": ["Collection of dehaloing VapourSynth functions"], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "vsdehalo._metadata.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "vsdehalo._metadata.__author__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "vsdehalo._metadata.__maintainer__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "vsdehalo", "documentation": ["ruff: noqa: F401, F403"], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "vsdehalo.alpha", "xref": {"fqname": "vsdehalo..alpha", "project": null}}, {"name": "vsdehalo.denoise", "xref": {"fqname": "vsdehalo..denoise", "project": null}}, {"name": "vsdehalo.warp", "xref": {"fqname": "vsdehalo..warp", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "vsdehalo.mask", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "vsdehalo.mask.base_dehalo_mask", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "src", "type": {"name": "vs.VideoNode", "xref": {"fqname": "vstools.vs.VideoNode", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "expand", "type": {"name": "float", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.float", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "iterations", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "brz0", "type": {"name": "float", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.float", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"nam